# Phase 15 — Cloudflare Runtime Drift SLA + Ownership Review Board

## Objective

Establish a scheduled drift review board, SLA classification for drift severity, an exception register, aging buckets for unresolved drift, and monthly governance evidence templates for the ZeaZ Platform Cloudflare runtime.

This phase must NOT deploy, apply, destroy, or mutate Cloudflare. It is a read-only governance documentation and scripting layer only.

---

## Branch Name

```
fix/cloudflare-runtime-drift-sla-review-board
```

## Commit Message

```
docs(cloudflare): add runtime drift sla and review board
```

---

## Scope

- Define SLA classes and aging buckets for all tracked Cloudflare drift items
- Establish ownership review board roles, responsibilities, and cadence
- Create exception register with required fields
- Create monthly governance evidence template
- Update infra/cloudflare/README.md with Phase 15 entry

---

## Non-Goals

- Do NOT run `wrangler deploy`, `terraform apply`, `tofu apply`, or any Cloudflare write
- Do NOT start or restart any services
- Do NOT edit `/etc/cloudflared/config.yml`
- Do NOT print, log, or commit any secrets or credentials
- Do NOT query live Cloudflare API unless explicitly enabled via opt-in flag
- Do NOT modify unrelated files or scopes

---

## Safety Rules

1. All scripts must be safe by default (offline/dry-run unless opt-in flag is passed)
2. Scripts must support `--help`, `--markdown`, `--json`, `--strict`
3. Never print `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN`, `TUNNEL_ID`, credentials, or any secret value
4. Treat all config files as potentially stale unless verified separately
5. All docs must clearly separate: live runtime facts | repo intent | Terraform ownership | manual actions | unresolved drift | evidence outputs
6. No exact-copy of live configuration — use sanitized examples only

---

