---

## Required Deliverables

### Documentation Files

1. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-runtime-drift-sla.md`**
   - SLA classes: Critical, High, Medium, Low, Accepted Exception
   - Aging buckets: 0–7 days, 8–14 days, 15–30 days, 31+ days
   - Escalation paths per SLA class
   - SLA breach definitions and consequences
   - Drift closure requirements

2. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-ownership-review-board.md`**
   - Review board roles:
     - Cloudflare runtime owner
     - DNS owner
     - Worker owner
     - Terraform owner
     - Security reviewer
     - Release approver
   - Meeting cadence (weekly, monthly, quarterly)
   - Quorum requirements
   - Voting / sign-off process
   - Escalation contacts
   - Board charter

3. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-drift-exception-register.md`**
   - Exception register table with fields:
     - Drift ID
     - System area (DNS / Tunnel / Worker / IaC / Access / Secret)
     - Owner
     - Reason
     - Risk level
     - Approval status
     - Expiry date
     - Next review date
     - Closure evidence reference
   - Example sanitized entries (no real values)
   - Process for adding, approving, renewing, and closing exceptions

4. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-monthly-governance-evidence.md`**
   - Template for monthly governance evidence including:
     - Period covered
     - Scanner output reference
     - Unresolved drift list
     - Accepted exceptions
     - Expired exceptions
     - Owner sign-off table
     - Summary of changes approved/rejected
     - Drift aging statistics

5. **`docs/infra/cloudflare-drift-report.md`** *(update if existing)*
   - Add SLA class field to each drift item
   - Add aging bucket field to each drift item
   - Add exception register reference where applicable

6. **`infra/cloudflare/README.md`** *(update)*
   - Add Phase 15 entry with links to all deliverables above

